Douyu, China's largest live-streaming platform focused on games, began trading on the NASDAQ on Wednesday. The shares, which went public at $11.50, closed flat. Douyu, backed by Chinese social media and gaming giant Tencent, said it expected to raise about $775 million through the IPO. Photo: IC  
